{{Infobox language |name=Balkan Gagauz Turkish |nativename=Rumeli Türkçesi |states=[[Turkey]], [[Bulgaria]], [[Republic of Macedonia|Macedonia]] |speakers=330,000 |date=1993 |ref=e18 |familycolor=Altaic |fam1=[[Turkic languages|Turkic]] |fam2=[[Common Turkic languages|Common Turkic]] |fam3=[[Oghuz languages|Oghuz]] |fam4=Turkish group |script = [[Latin script]], [[Cyrillic alphabet]] |iso3=bgx |glotto=balk1254 |glottorefname=Balkan Gagauz Turkish }}
'''Balkan Gagauz Turkish''', also known as '''Balkan Turkic''', is a [[Turkic languages|Turkic]] language spoken in [[East Thrace|European Turkey]], in [[Dulovo, Bulgaria|Dulovo]] and the [[Deliorman]] area in [[Bulgaria]], and in the [[Kumanovo]] and [[Bitola]] areas of the [[Republic of Macedonia]].<ref name=Ethnologue>[http://www.ethnologue.com/show_language.asp?code=bgx Ethnologue entry for Balkan Gagauz Turkish]</ref> Dialects include [[Gajal]], Gerlovo Turk, Karamanli, Kyzylbash, Surguch, Tozluk Turk, Yuruk, and Macedonian Gagauz. Although it is mutually intelligible with both [[Gagauz language|Gagauz]]<ref name=Ethnologue/> and [[Turkish language|Turkish]] to a considerable degree, it is usually classified as a separate language due to foreign influences from neighboring languages spoken in the [[Balkans]].
