The '''Chu''' language is an attested language spoken during the [[Chu (state)|Chu state]] of China, and is believed to be the base precursor to [[Xiang Chinese]], a dialect spoken in [[Hunan]]. The Chu had its own characters modeled on Zhou dynasty Chinese characters.<ref>Park, Haeree. "Recent Advances in Old Chinese Historical Phonology", Society of Oriental and African Studies, University of London.</ref> 

