'''Hayden Kays''' (born 3 October 1985 in [[London]]) is a British artist. He is influenced by the pop art from the '50s, but has most ties with street art. Banksy is a fan.{{citation needed|date=September 2014}}
He often uses a typewriter (font) in his artworks.  In February 2014 he became well known for selling artwork to [[One Direction]] popstar [[Harry Styles]].<ref>{{cite web|website=Daily Mail|url=http://www.dailymail.co.uk/tvshowbiz/article-2550986/Harry-Styles-spends-20k-love-sex-related-artwork-including-If-I-wasnt-straight-Id-gay-poster.html|title=EXCLUSIVE: Harry Styles spends £20k on love and sex related artwork including 'If I wasn't straight I'd be gay' poster}}</ref> He has since sold art to celebrities such as [[Chris Martin]] <ref>{{cite web|website=eonline|url=http://uk.eonline.com/news/571369/jennifer-lawrence-and-chris-martin-enjoy-super-romantic-vineyard-date-get-the-scoop|title=Jennifer Lawrence and Chris Martin Enjoy "Super-Romantic" Vineyard Date: Get the Scoop!}}</ref> and [[Noel Fielding]].<ref>{{cite web|website=the arcadia online|url=http://www.thearcadiaonline.com/faces-to-watch-hayden-kays-the-artist-and-the-anarchist/|title=Faces to Watch: Hayden Kays, the artist and the anarchist}}</ref>

His works were collected in a monograph book in 2013, named Hayden Kays Is An Artist. ({{ISBN|978-0992726706}})

In 2014, he made the cover art for rock bands [[The Kooks]]  and the [[Tribes (band)]].<ref>{{cite web|website=the arcadia online|url=http://www.thearcadiaonline.com/faces-to-watch-hayden-kays-the-artist-and-the-anarchist/|title=Faces to Watch: Hayden Kays, the artist and the anarchist}}</ref>

